CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 31, 1956, pg. A39, reads: "Concert Soloists - James Lumberger, left, counter tenor, and Henry Spinelli, right, pianist, will solo individually at the Mozart Festival Concert, presented by the Junior Friends of Music, April 4, at 8:30 P.M., in Carnegie Hall, Oakland. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Singer James Lumberger and pianist Henry Spinelli, holding music book titled "Ausgewahlte Kammermusik, W.A. Mozart Trio NR. IV (Kegelstatt Trio . 498)...," in interior with oval mirror
